  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Exactly I want something like this @vvo \n\n``` javascript\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.hierarchicalMenu({\n    container: '#categories',\n    attributes: [ 'category','sub_category','sub_sub_category'],\n    sortBy: [custom,'name:asc','count:desc']\n  })\n);\n```\n\nAnd I achieved this by writing the code below, maybe it can help someone else.\n\n##### Example Category Tree\n- Clothing\n  - Clothing > Dresses\n    - Clothing > Dresses > Mini Dresses\n    - Clothing > Dresses > Midi Dresses\n  - Clothing > Tops\n  - Clothing > Bottoms\n  - Clothing > Outwears\n- Accessories\n  - Accessories > Jewelery\n  - Accessories > Bags\n\n##### Javascript\n\n``` javascript\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.hierarchicalMenu({\n    container: '#categories',\n    attributes: [ 'category','sub_category','sub_sub_category'],\n    sortBy: customSort\n  })\n);\nvar categories = [\"Clothing\", \"Clothing > Dresses\", \"Clothing > Dresses > Mini Dresses\", \"Clothing > Dresses > Midi Dresses\",...];\nfunction customSort(a,b){\n    if(a.path.split(\">\").length==1){ //category\n        return categories.indexOf(a.path) - categories.indexOf(b.path);\n    }else if(a.path.split(\">\").length==2){ //sub_category\n        return a.name > b.name;\n    }else{\n         //sub_sub_category\n        return a.count < b.count;\n    }\n}\n```\n",
    "created_at": "2016-04-15T16:15:06Z",
